ZH: 请务必听从我的指示。
EN: Please make sure to obey my instructions.

ZH: 他们不愿意听从我的建议。
EN: They are unwilling to listen to my advice.

ZH: 我们必须听从规定的安全指引。
EN: We must adhere to the specified safety guidelines.

ZH: 作为领导人，他们必须学会听从团队成员的意见。
EN: As leaders, they must learn to heed the opinions of team members.

ZH: 他一直都很擅长听从命令。
EN: He has always been good at following orders.

ZH: 孩子们总是很乖，听从父母的安排。
EN: The children are always well-behaved and comply with their parents' arrangements.

ZH: 这是他们应当听从的命令。
EN: This is the order they should comply with.

ZH: 她经常不愿意听从老师的要求。
EN: She often refuses to comply with the teacher's requests.

ZH: 在这种情况下，我们必须听从领导的决定。
EN: In this situation, we must obey the leader's decision.

ZH: 他一直都是一个很好听从别人的人。
EN: He has always been someone who is good at following others.

ZH: 请向他们解释为什么需要听从警告。
EN: Please explain to them why it is necessary to heed the warning.

ZH: 她总是很听从祖父母的劝告。
EN: She always listens to her grandparents' advice.

ZH: 对于自我安全，请听从导游的指示。
EN: For your own safety, please obey the tour guide's instructions.

ZH: 你们需要听从我们的安排。
EN: You need to comply with our arrangements.

ZH: 我不知道为什么他们不愿意听从规则。
EN: I don't know why they are unwilling to obey the rules.

ZH: 你必须听从规定的程序。
EN: You must adhere to the prescribed procedures.

ZH: 这是他们的基本要求，请不要拒绝听从。
EN: This is their basic requirement, please do not refuse to comply.

ZH: 我们必须听从时间表上的安排。
EN: We must adhere to the arrangements on the schedule.

ZH: 她今天态度很差，不愿意听从任何人。
EN: She has a bad attitude today and is unwilling to listen to anyone.

ZH: 对于紧急情况，请务必听从导火索。
EN: In case of an emergency, please obey the fuse.
